Thirteen suspected illegal immigrants from Ethiopia were spotted running from the back of a lorry on a busy motorway today.

Rush-hour traffic had to be slowed between junctions 12 and 13 of the M25 in Surrey as police dealt with the incident this morning, although officers arrived after the lorry had driven from the scene.

However the 13 men and women were found walking along the motorway and were arrested on suspicion of immigration offences. They are now being held in custody by Surrey Police.

