The arrests came three days after a man was detained for alleged ‘facilitation offences’ after 24 Eritrean nationals were discovered in the rear of an HGV in Whitfield, near Dover, Kent.

Paramedics from South East Coast Ambulance Service checked them over at the scene but none needed hospital treatment.

